The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Waugh backs Ricky 
                                                   Waugh backs Ricky 
                      
	Melbourne: Ricky Pontings decision to skip the Indian Premier League (IPL) and focus his energies on international commitments was a smart move, feels Steve Waugh.         
	Ponting, contracted with the Kolkata Knight Riders, has opted out of the second season, saying he wouldnt be able to give his all to the national team if he uses the two-week break to play in the IPL.         
	Waugh backed Pontings decision.         
	Financially, guys do pretty well these days, so I think its a smart move.         
	Hes the captain of Australia, a lot of responsibilities, its going to be a tough 12 months coming up, Waugh was quoted as saying by a news agency, here.           (PTI)                                                                                                                   
